Hi, I’ve been having an issue that I get ‘no robot code’ when deploying the code to the robot. After testing, I pinpointed the issue to the YAGSL config files as the code moved when deploying with an old config that had bad values. However, after changing the config to make it move properly, whenever I enabled the program, the motors wouldn’t do anything, and the RIOlog would say ‘No robot code is deployed’ despite the driver station letting me enable the robot. I have tried regenerating the config files, but it doesn’t seem to work. How can I fix the issue so I can move the robot again? I have attached the zip file for the config.
swerve.zip (3.1 KB)

Just in case you don’t already know about this, here’s the official YAGSL Tuning Webpage so you can confirm all your values are valid and formatted correctly. I may be wrong, but I think it’s safe to say that if you plug in all your info to the tuning webpage and use the config it generates, and you’re still having the issue, it’s not the config. (Unless YAGSL has some ongoing issue that I’m not aware about) Make sure to check for any other errors being thrown when you run the code. Is it going back and forth periodically from green to red on the “Robot Code” indicator on the Driver Station?

enishangck:

can you change “falcon” to “talonfx” Because in yagsl it is not falcon but talonfx, falcon engines use talonfx drivers anyway

I don’t know too much about this because our team uses Spark MAXs, but in the aforementioned YAGSL Tuning Webpage, selecting “Falcon500” for drive motor results in “falcon” in the config file. I checked all the motor options on that webpage and none of them result in “talonfx” in the config.
